# Plan: .mdu Runtime Plugin Module System

## TL;DR
Replace the hard-coded, switch-case module dispatch system with a runtime plugin architecture.
.mdu files are valid C++ source files with a structured metadata comment block at the top.
At startup (and live on save), the app compiles each .mdu to a .so via g++, loads it via dlopen,
and registers the module without requiring a full rebuild. Existing modules are rewritten as .mdu.

---

## Decisions
- Loading: runtime dlopen + both startup load AND inotify file-watcher live reload
- Header format: /*! MODULE ... */ block comment (valid C++, easy to parse, no extra tooling)
- Module body: free-form C++, implements MduModule virtual base class, uses MDU_REGISTER macro to export factory symbols
- Directories: scan src/Modules/ always + user-configurable extra path (saved in config file, editable in UI)
- Migration: all 5 existing modules rewritten as .mdu; old .cpp modules deleted
- API design: virtual MduModule base class (mdu_api.h), MDU_REGISTER macro, MduBuffer/MduPin structs (decide details during implementation)

---

## Phase 1 - Module SDK (mdu_api.h + types)

1. Create `include/mdu_api.h`:
	- `MduMetadata` struct: name, type_string, version, author, ins (vector<MduPin>), outs (vector<MduPin>), params (vector<MduParamDef>), dependencies
	- `MduPin` struct: id, label
	- `MduParamDef` struct: id, label, type (knob/stepped/combo), min, max, default_val, options (for combo)
	- `MduBuffer` struct: input float* arrays indexed by pin id, output float* arrays indexed by pin id, num_samples, sample_rate, cv_inputs map
	- `MduModule` abstract base class: virtual process(MduBuffer&), virtual drawEditor(), virtual std::string getParamAsString(id), virtual void setParam(id, float)
	- `MDU_REGISTER(ClassName)` macro: generates extern "C" { MduModule* mdu_create(); void mdu_destroy(MduModule*); MduMetadata* mdu_get_metadata(); }

2. Create `include/MduParser.h` / `src/MduParser.cpp`:
	- `ParseMduHeader(filepath)` -> MduMetadata: reads file, finds /*! MODULE ... */, parses YAML-like fields
	- Does NOT require compiling; metadata is available for UI before load

## Phase 2 - ModuleLoader system

3. Create `include/ModuleLoader.h` / `src/ModuleLoader.cpp`:
	- Scans `src/Modules/` + configurable extra path for *.mdu files
	- Compiles each: `g++ -shared -fPIC -std=c++17 {include_flags} {mdu_file} -o {cache_dir}/{name}.so`
	- Include flags must cover: project include/, imgui, implot, imnodes, SDL2
	- Cache dir: `build/mdu_cache/`
	- dlopen each .so, dlsym for mdu_create, mdu_destroy, mdu_get_metadata
	- Stores: map<string, LoadedModule> where LoadedModule = {soHandle, MduMetadata, factories}
	- `ReloadModule(path)`: destroy old instance, dlclose, recompile, dlopen new version
	- `GetAvailableModuleTypes()` -> list of MduMetadata for "Add Module" menu

4. Create file watcher (inotify on Linux):
	- Background thread watches src/Modules/ and extra path
	- On IN_CLOSE_WRITE for a .mdu file -> post reload event to main thread queue
	- Main thread processes queue at frame start (safe to reload before audio update)
	- Thread-safe: use SDL_LockAudioDevice / SDL_UnlockAudioDevice to pause audio during swap

## Phase 3 - Refactor core data structures

5. Replace `Module` struct in `include/Functions/Module.h`:
	- New `DynamicModule` struct: int ID, string name, bool active, MduMetadata metadata, MduModule* instance, void* soHandle
	- Keep `ModuleType` enum for now as a parsed enum from metadata type_string (for backward compat with imnodes pin math)
	- Replace VCOConfig/LFOConfig/etc. union with MduModule* instance (state lives in the subclass)

6. Update `Rack` struct in `Handler.h`:
	- Change `vector<Module>` -> `vector<DynamicModule>`
	- Links stay the same (still use moduleID x 1000 + pinIdx encoding)

## Phase 4 - Refactor Handler dispatch

7. Refactor `Handler.cpp`:
	- `AddModuleToRack(typeId)` -> looks up factory by typeId string, calls mdu_create(), appends DynamicModule
	- `RemoveModuleFromRack(id)` -> calls mdu_destroy(), dlclose only if last user of that .so
	- `AudioFilterCallback()`: remove switch-case, call `module.instance->process(buf)` for each module
	- `UpdateAudioWaveFormsFromRacks()`: GenerateLFOOutputs, BuildNormalizedCVInputs still needed but use MduModule API for output access
	- `GenerateLFOOutputs()`: instead of switching on LFO type, call `instance->process(buf)` then call `instance->getOutputBuffer(pinIdx)`

8. Refactor `ModuleEditor.cpp`:
	- `DrawModuleEditorWindow(DynamicModule&)` -> draw common header, then call `module.instance->drawEditor()`
	- Remove all type-specific draw calls

9. Refactor `WaveFormGenerator.cpp` (VCO handling):
	- VCO .mdu will fill the output buffer via process(); Handler reads it as a WaveForm-equivalent
	- Decide: either keep WaveForm struct as the VCO output format (easiest migration), or generalize to MduBuffer pin outputs

## Phase 5 - Rewrite existing modules as .mdu

Each file in modules/ (new top-level dir):

10. `modules/vco.mdu` - Voltage Controlled Oscillator
	 - Header: type=VCO, 4 inputs, 3 outputs, params: coarseTune/octave/fineTune/fmDepth/waveform/voltageRange
	 - Body: copy GetWaveFormData() logic from WaveForm.cpp, drawEditor from WaveFormGenerator.cpp

11. `modules/lfo.mdu` - Low Frequency Oscillator
	 - Header: type=LFO, 2 inputs, 3 outputs, params: frequency/amplitude/waveform
	 - Body: copy LFO processing + draw from LowFrequencyOscillator.cpp

12. `modules/vcf.mdu` - Voltage Controlled Filter
	 - Header: type=VCF, 3 inputs, 1 output, params: cutoff/resonance/filterType
	 - Body: copy ProcessAudio + draw from VoltageControllFilter.cpp

13. `modules/vca.mdu` - Voltage Controlled Amplifier
	 - Header: type=VCA, 2 inputs, 1 output, params: baseGain/cvAmount/attack/release
	 - Body: copy ProcessAudioWithCVBuffer + draw from Voltage-ControlledAmplifier.cpp

14. `modules/output.mdu` - Audio Output
	 - Header: type=OUTPUT, 1 input, 0 outputs, params: outputLevel
	 - Body: copy ProcessAudio + draw from Output.cpp

## Phase 6 - Configuration & UI

15. `src/Config.cpp` / `include/Config.h`:
	 - Load/save config.ini (or reuse imgui.ini sidecar): stores extra_mdu_path
	 - `GetExtraMduPath()` / `SetExtraMduPath(path)`

16. UI additions in `Handler.cpp` (or `Window.cpp`):
	 - "Add Module" menu: populated from ModuleLoader.GetAvailableModuleTypes()
	 - Settings window: text input for extra .mdu search directory + "Rescan" button
	 - Status bar: show last reload event ("vco.mdu reloaded @ 14:32:01")

## Phase 7 - CMakeLists.txt updates

17. Remove source file references for old module .cpp files
18. Add `build/mdu_cache/` as output dir (or ensure it is created at runtime)
19. No CMake changes needed for .mdu compilation (it's runtime g++), but ensure include paths are accessible
20. Add `dl` to linked libraries (`target_link_libraries(... dl)`)

---

## Relevant files to modify/create

- `include/mdu_api.h` - NEW: module SDK
- `include/MduParser.h` + `src/MduParser.cpp` - NEW: header parser
- `include/ModuleLoader.h` + `src/ModuleLoader.cpp` - NEW: loader + file watcher
- `include/Config.h` + `src/Config.cpp` - NEW: config persistence
- `include/Functions/Module.h` - REPLACE Module/ModuleType with DynamicModule
- `include/Handler.h` - Update Rack to use DynamicModule
- `src/Modules/Handler.cpp` - Major refactor: remove switch-case dispatch
- `src/Modules/ModuleEditor.cpp` - Simplify: delegate to instance->drawEditor()
- `src/Modules/WaveFormGenerator.cpp` - Refactor VCO/LFO handling for dynamic dispatch
- `CMakeLists.txt` - Add dl library, remove old module sources
- `modules/vco.mdu` - NEW
- `modules/lfo.mdu` - NEW
- `modules/vcf.mdu` - NEW
- `modules/vca.mdu` - NEW
- `modules/output.mdu` - NEW
- Delete: `src/Modules/LowFrequencyOscillator.cpp`, `VoltageControllFilter.cpp`, `Voltage-ControlledAmplifier.cpp`, `Output.cpp`, `WaveFormGenerator.cpp`

---

## Verification

1. Run CMake build - only Signals binary (no .so yet, those are runtime-compiled)
2. Launch app - check that src/Modules/*.mdu files are discovered, compiled, and loaded
3. Open "Add Module" menu - VCO, LFO, VCF, VCA, Output appear
4. Create a VCO -> VCF -> VCA -> Output patch and verify audio output
5. Edit vco.mdu coarseTune default value while app is running -> save -> verify it hot-reloads without crash
6. Add a .mdu file to the user-configured extra path -> rescan -> module appears
7. Check imnodes patching still works (pin ID encoding unchanged)
8. Verify audio thread safety: no crashes when reloading during audio playback
